socket99
------------------------------------------
Wrapper library for the BSD sockets API with a nicer C99 interface

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.4-1
  libsocket99-devel-0.2.0-1bl1
  libsocket99_0-0.2.0-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/silentbicycle/socket99

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/silentbicycle/socket99/archive/v0.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack socket99-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./socket99-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/socket99-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/socket99-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsocket99_0-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsocket99-devel-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(socket99)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/socket99.README
  /usr/share/doc/socket99/README.md

(libsocket99_0)
  /usr/bin/cygsocket99-0.dll

(libsocket99-devel)
  /usr/include/socket99.h
  /usr/lib/libsocket99.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/socket99.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

